The paper discusses a novel self-interference cancellation structure for in-band MIMO full-duplex transceivers, which involves utilizing reference receiver chains for obtaining reference signals for digital self-interference cancellation. This involves analyzing the achievable performance of the proposed cancellation scheme, providing a detailed formulation of the cancellation procedure, and assessing the achieved performance with full waveform simulations. The paper thus falls under the broad category of Information Theory (cs.IT), as it deals with signal processing and communication in wireless networks. It also involves aspects of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), as it deals with the design and optimization of wireless network architectures. The paper also involves aspects of Systems and Control (cs.SY), as it deals with the control and optimization of wireless communication systems. Additionally, the paper involves aspects of Multimedia (cs.MM), as it deals with the processing and transmission of multimedia signals in wireless networks. Finally, the paper also involves aspects of Computer Communications (cs.COM), as it deals with the design and optimization of communication protocols and architectures in wireless networks.
